margaret richardson  wikipedia margaret richardson from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from margaret milner richardson jump to navigation search for other people named margaret richardson see margaret richardson disambiguation margaret milner peggy richardson born  may  is an american lawyer and former commissioner of internal revenue at the internal revenue service irs from  to  life and careeredit a native of waco texas she earned an undergraduate degree in political science from vassar college in  and a jd with honors from the george washington university law school in  she married lawyer john l richardson in  and has one daughter she is a member of the district of columbia and virginia bars and is a fellow of the american bar foundation richardson clerked at the us court of claims before joining the office of chief counsel of the irs eventually becoming the first woman promoted to executive rank in that offices history in  richardson joined law firm sutherland asbill and brennan in washington dc becoming a partner in  until her  irs appointment during her tenure she was appointed to the irs commissioners advisory group serving as a member from  to  and as chair from  to  following her service as irs commissioner richardson became a member of ernst  young in washington dc from december  to  she has since served on the boards of jackson hewitt tax service inc and legg mason richardson is coauthor of several editions of the ernst  young tax savers guide referencesedit  gilpin kenneth l february   clinton picks lawyer to be irs chief  new york times  richardson margaret milner and peter w bernstein  the ernst  young tax savers guide  john wiley  sons isbn   richardson margaret milner and peter w bernstein  the ernst  young tax savers guide  john wiley  sons asin bjbaobe  richardson margaret milner and peter w bernstein  the ernst  young tax savers guide  wiley isbn  external linksedit margaret milner richardson profile via forbes retrieved from httpsen