l virginians for sensible energy policies and the national museum of women in the arts previously she spent several years as a tax partner  at ernst  young where she served as the national director of irs practice and procedure prior to that she headed the internal revenue service from  until  as commissioner and served on the internal revenue service commissioners advisory group from  to  and chaired the group in  as commissioner she worked on tax administration and taxpayer service while also working with tax administrators in foreign jurisdictions previously ms richardson worked at a private firm in washington prior to that she clerked at the us court of claims and then joined the office of chief counsel of the internal revenue service previously she served as a director of jackson hewitt tax service inc from june  through august  she also served on the boards of several nonprofit organizations including usa for unhcr which she chaired the womens campaign fund the fishing school and the national cathedral school for girls where she served as president of the parents association ms richardson is a member of the district of columbia and virginia bars a fellow of the american bar foundation and on the aliaba advisory panel on business and corporate law she is also a member of the washington womens forum and the international womens forum ms richardson was named woman of the year by the financial womens association and she is the recipient of the federal bar association section of taxations kenneth liles distinguished service award the tax executives institute distinguished service award and the hartford institute award she was named a washington woman of genius by trinity college ms richardson graduated from vassar college with a degree in political science and received her jd with honors from the george washington university law schoolread full background corporate headquarters  sylvan wayparsippany new jersey united statesphone fax  board members memberships prese